  "finding": "Explicit ylong_base runtime worker configuration is not a SOTA lever for this workload. It helps HTTP-over-HTTPS-proxy throughput, but the full fair matrix still fails fixed SOTA gates: throughput geomean is only 1.006x, worst throughput is 0.686x, p95 geomean regresses to 1.075x, CPU/request geomean regresses to 1.269x, and RSS max is 1.165x. The strongest counterexamples are the 1000-request HTTPS-origin proxy cells, where nested TLS p50/p95 and CPU regress heavily. Because the change is benchmark-harness-only and does not satisfy S9, it is rejected and not retained.",
